In English-Speaking countries, cacao is called cocoa. Ghana is the world's second largest cacao/cocoa bean producer. The beans are usually sold to international traders who then uses them to make chocolate.

Cocoa is the chief agricultural export of Ghana and the country's main cash crop. All cocoa beans produced in the country must be sold to licensed buyers or the government agency called Cocoa Marketing Board. All international exports are controlled by the government of Ghana, but there are around 25 private companies buying the crop in all areas of the country. Farmers are guaranteed a minimum floor price (cocoa minimum price: 1,700 American Dollars per metric ton). I am looking for reliable investors to help me grow this cocoa farming company in Ghana.

Save and pay two to three years’ rent.

name: SnooCODE
product_desc:
SnooCODE, the flagship product from tinyDAVID, is a fit for purpose solution for economic and social development in the developing world.

A SnooCODE is a 6 or 7-digit alphanumeric geolocation code that acts like a UK post code or a US Zip Code except over 200 x more precise. It can be used to provide directions to any location and is accurate to within less than 7 metres.

SnooCODEs are simple, easy to remember for nations operating in different languages. The application can work offline, without credit or connection to a network, allowing it to be robust even when the infrastructure is not.

The problem that SnooCODE solves is bigger than not knowing where people are located. We provide a technology to support poor countries in leapfrogging traditional systems, on which we can build to answer their specific needs and help them cheetah charge towards world-class standards.

The SnooCODE is completely free and is available to download on iOS and Android.

name: Liezer - Legacy Productions

Liezer-Legacy Productions is an arts organization that is dedicated to creating and producing theatrical works of comedy and comedic works that explore and celebrate our sense of humanity and history as Ghanaians and Africans.
We produce at least 8 mainstream Theatre productions. We also host and produce 2 shows every week on live radio; a political satire show, The PM Show, on Luv 99.5 FM Thursdays at 8 pm and a comedy radio drama show in our local language (Twi) which addresses social issues on Nhyira 104.5 FM Saturdays at 7:15 pm. The Acting school offers students training in stage acting, screen acting, dance and vocal training. name: InvestED, PBC
product_desc:
InvestED’s platform provides entrepreneurship training for grassroots business owners in emerging markets. We generate sales leads for microfinance institutions (MFIs) and help them digitally manage their portfolio.

Our Android app provides users with engaging lessons which help them gain points towards an alternative credit score. We also link users based on location in order to create community and verify that they are not scammers. Our cloud-based analytic engine rates the user based on their performance within our curriculum, combined with real-world indicators, and aggregate loan performance. This populates our MFI facing dashboard. Loan officers use this tool to shop for borrowers. The loan is originated and repaid through the platform via mobile money.

InvestED will bridge the gap between the inherent entrepreneurial drive of small business owners in our target market, and the lack of access to education and startup capital they need to be successful.
markets: Education, Education Technology, Social Enterprise, Fin Tech

name: Green Solar Africa
product_desc:
GSA provides off-grid solar power systems in four sizes. The smaller power solutions such as the 1kW and 2kW systems can provide enough energy for a small home that utilizes few appliances. This size system can be used to power a refrigerator throughout the day, along with lighting for 2-3 rooms, fans, and small electronic devices. It can also service momentary larger draws of power such as electricity needed for a small washing machine, blow dryers, microwave, and a TV.

The medium sized system is a 3kW system that provides energy to support longer duration energy needs. This system can be used to run a refrigerator or freezer, regular use of an air conditioner, and intermittent use of lights, electronics, TV, and washing machine.

The larger system is a 5kW system that can support regular use of air conditioner to cool the home throughout the day, refrigerator or freezer, lighting, TV, electronics, and increased use of washing machines, microwaves, and electric ovens.
markets: Solar, Residential Solar, Concentrated Solar Power

Put together, our product is similar to Eventbrite with the transportation solution in-built.

name: AIRQUALITY
product_desc:
An air sanitizer is a sanitizer that acts on airborne microbiological organisms or microorganisms.  It is a disinfectant that disinfect, sanitize, reduce and mitigating growth or development of microbiological organisms including bacteria, fungi or viruses in the household, institutional, and/or commercial environment.

Unlike air purifiers, which filter or otherwise trap particles within an air circulator, air sanitizers have the ability to act on airborne microorganisms in open interior air space. A sneeze- or cough-generated pathogenic aerosol will take significant time to be treated by a circulating air purifier simply because air circulators are unable to treat all of the room air simultaneously.

Bamboo bicycles are comparable or superior to current steel and carbon fiber bicycles both in terms of quality and suitability for multiple rider needs. name: Meltwater Foundation (MEST)

Students from Ghana, Nigeria, South Africa, Kenya and Côte d'Ivoire come to the MEST Campus in Ghana to learn the skills required to launch globally successful software companies.

Founded in Accra, Ghana in 2008, MEST is the brainchild of CEO Jorn Lyseggen, who believes that talented people are everywhere, and with the right nurturing, support, and guidance, the next Facebook or Google can come from Africa.

Today, over 400 individual entrepreneurs have graduated from the training program and over 25 tech companies have been launched via seed funding and mentorship from MEST, which is a huge success and a great development for the African economy.

name: Farmerline
product_desc:
Smallholder farmers lack sufficient access to timely and locally relevant information, resulting in lower yields and high post-harvest losses. 

To address this challenge, Farmerline Ltd has developed a mobile-web based application that communicates timely and relevant agricultural information (such as weather alerts, best farm practices, financial tips, market prices and market access) through recorded voice messages to farmers’ mobile phones. The messages are sent in local languages and can be used to support NGOs and agricultural organizations as they deliver services and collect data. 

Farmerline’s voice technology does not only bridge the illiteracy barrier but it also reduces the cost of communication and data collection for small-scale farmers and organizations working with them. Our vision is to improve livelihoods for farmers through technology and increased access to information.
high_concept: Using ICTs to communicate audio content to smallholder farmers across West Africa
